    "body": "Safemath is a pretty easy thing, basically just assertions that the math won't overflow before you do the math e.g. `assert a-b == -(b-a)` for `a-b` (or something like that). We can probably adopt the solidity safe math library pretty easily.\r\n\r\nIt's more a strategic issue to me. Do we want to enforce **all** math to be safe math, therefore adding extra assertion code and costing extra gas? I believe for Viper that answer is yes, but I wanted to clarify this point.",
